# QA Code Review Testing (Phase 2)

When reviewing `.kt` changes, actively hunt for defects — do not approve by default.

## Crash Risks
- [ ] Nullable access without safe calls (`!!`, unchecked `getString()`)
- [ ] `IllegalStateException` from wrong lifecycle or NavController state
- [ ] Index out of bounds on lists/collections
- [ ] Coroutine launched after `ViewModel` cleared / not tied to `viewModelScope`
- [ ] Collecting Flow without lifecycle awareness in UI
- [ ] Navigation with missing or malformed args (`navArgument`, `savedStateHandle`)

## Architecture (Testability Impact)
- [ ] Business logic in Composables (hard to test, regression-prone)
- [ ] ViewModel bypassing use cases
- [ ] Untestable static/singleton dependencies

## Security
- [ ] Hardcoded API keys, tokens, PINs
- [ ] Logging PII (mobile, CNIC, balance, card numbers)
- [ ] Sensitive data in `savedStateHandle` without encryption
- [ ] Missing SSL / certificate pinning for financial APIs

## Performance
- [ ] API called on every recomposition
- [ ] Blocking call on Main Thread
- [ ] Unbounded list without `LazyColumn` + `key`
- [ ] Large object creation in hot paths

## State Handling (Functional Gaps)
- [ ] Missing loading state for async operations
- [ ] Missing error state / retry for `ResponseStates.Failure`
- [ ] Missing empty state
- [ ] Double-tap / rapid click not debounced on payment actions

## Regression Triggers
- [ ] Shared ViewModel scope changed
- [ ] Navigation route or arg key renamed
- [ ] `ResponseStates` handling altered
- [ ] New interceptor or header logic

Flag each finding with severity and a concrete test case to reproduce.
